methods.name: public Builder setOrg(@OrganizationCode int orgCode)
methods.comment:
* Sets the organization code * * @param orgCode the organization code with the following value *
    *
  1. {@link #ORG_NONE}
    2. *
  2. {@link #ORG_3GPP}
    3. *
  3. {@link #ORG_3GPP2}
    4. *
  4. {@link #ORG_OMA}
    5. *
  5. {@link #ORG_GSMA}
    6. *
  6. {@link #ORG_LOCAL}
    7. *
* @throws IllegalArgumentException if it is not one of the value above. * *

Note that this method will reset the security protocol and TLS cipher suite * if they have been set.

methods.name: public Builder setProtocol(@UaSecurityProtocol3gpp int protocol)
methods.comment:
* Sets the UA security protocol for 3GPP * * @param protocol only 3GPP ua security protocol ID is supported for now, which * is one of the following value *
    *
  1. {@link #UA_SECURITY_PROTOCOL_3GPP_SUBSCRIBER_CERTIFICATE}
    2. *
  2. {@link #UA_SECURITY_PROTOCOL_3GPP_MBMS}
    3. *
  3. {@link #UA_SECURITY_PROTOCOL_3GPP_HTTP_DIGEST_AUTHENTICATION}
    4. *
  4. {@link #UA_SECURITY_PROTOCOL_3GPP_HTTP_BASED_MBMS}
    5. *
  5. {@link #UA_SECURITY_PROTOCOL_3GPP_SIP_BASED_MBMS}
    6. *
  6. {@link #UA_SECURITY_PROTOCOL_3GPP_GENERIC_PUSH_LAYER}
    7. *
  7. {@link #UA_SECURITY_PROTOCOL_3GPP_IMS_MEDIA_PLANE}
    8. *
  8. {@link #UA_SECURITY_PROTOCOL_3GPP_GENERATION_TMPI}
    9. *
  9. {@link #UA_SECURITY_PROTOCOL_3GPP_TLS_DEFAULT}
    10. *
  10. {@link #UA_SECURITY_PROTOCOL_3GPP_TLS_BROWSER}
    11. *
* @throws IllegalArgumentException if the protocol is not one of the value above. * *

Note that this method will reset TLS cipher suite if it has been set.

methods.name: public Builder setTlsCipherSuite(@TlsCipherSuite int cs)
methods.comment:
* Sets the UA security protocol for 3GPP
         *
         * @param cs TLS cipher suite value defined by {@link TlsParams#TlsCipherSuite}
         * @throws IllegalArgumentException if it is not a 3GPP ua security protocol,
         * the protocol does not support TLS, or does not support the cipher suite.
